dcterms:description: CheXpert is a publicly available Pre-training dataset developed by the Stanford University School of Medicine. This dataset contains a vast collection of 224,316 chest X-rays obtained from 65,240 patients. It includes labeled information from free-text reports describing the presence of 14 common chest diseases and findings in the images, such as pneumonia, nodules, cardiopulmonary enlargement, and more.
dcterms:title: CheXpert

dcterms:description: MIMIC-CXR (Medical Information Mart for Intensive Care - Chest X-ray) is another Pre-training dataset containing nearly 227,835 chest X-ray images, each of which corresponds to a text report from various US medical institutions.
dcterms:title: MIMIC-CXR

dcterms:description: CheXpert-5x200 is a multi-class classification dataset sampled from the testing split of CheXpert, including classes such as Atelectasis, Cardiomegaly, Edema, and Pleural Effusion, with each class containing 200 positive samples.
dcterms:title: CheXpert-5x200

dcterms:description: MIMIC-5x200 is a dataset sampled for evaluation from MIMIC-CXR, focusing on the same five tasks as CheXpert-5x200.
dcterms:title: MIMIC-5x200

dcterms:description: This dataset was collected from several hospitals in QATAR, containing approximately equal numbers of COVID and non-COVID tagged cases. A balanced subset for COVID-19 and Non-COVID-19 was sampled for 2000 samples.
dcterms:title: COVID-19

dcterms:description: The RSNA pneumonia dataset, published by the Radiological Society of North America (RSNA) in 2018, contains 26,684 chest X-ray images of patients with pneumonia and normal people of different ages, genders, and races. A balanced subset for pneumonia and non-pneumonia was sampled for evaluation.
dcterms:title: RSNA pneumonia
